Usage: pin COMMAND [ARGS]

Pin helps you organize your commands. COMMAND can be one of the
following:

You can directly pass the index of the command or the SHA1 to run
the command.

   ls [CATEGORY]	List all commands. Optionally pass category
   rm CMD		Remove a specific command
   sync			Sync commands
   import URL		Import a new command from url
   export		Export a saved command as url
   grep TERM		Search commands matching the passed term
   desc CMD		Describe a saved command
   watch CMD		Watch a command
   run CMD		Run a command
   tags CMD		Show all tags
   dump CMD		Dump command / script or blob to stdout
   fork CMD		Fork a command to create a new one
   save-cmd STRING	Save a new command
   save-blob		Save a new blob from stdin
   save-script		Save a new script from stdin
   create-script	Open editor to create and save a new script
   create-blob		Open editor to create and save a new blob
   create-cmd		Open editor to create and save a new command
   copy [FILE]		Copy from stdin to cl1p.net. Optionally copy file if passed.
   paste		Paste from cl1p.net to stdout
   usage-full		Full usage with advanced commands
   categories		Show all categories
   version		Show pin version
